{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Tet Layer"], "type": "title", "extent": [141, 155], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [155, 221], "text": ["Creates a layer of tetrahedra adjacent to a polygon mesh."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [221, 640], "text": ["The Tet Layer SOP creates a layer of tetrahedra that are adjacent to the input polygon mesh. The resulting tet mesh can be used to simulate skin and fat layers in a muscle sim, for example using the ", {"text": ["FEM Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/femsolver", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/femsolver"}, " or the ", {"text": ["Vellum Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/vellumsolver", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/vellumsolver"}, ". Tet Layer turns a polygonal sphere into a hollow ball, whereas ", {"text": ["Tet Conform"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tetconform", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/tetconform"}, " turns a polygonal sphere into a solid ball."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [640, 771], "text": ["The tetrahedra share the polygon points. This SOP is not limited to triangular polygons; it may be used with quadrangles as well."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [776, 930], "text": ["For building good quality simulation meshes, we recommend that you apply a ", {"text": ["Remesh SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/remesh", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/remesh"}, " to your polygonal geometry before Tet Layer."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [771, 776], "container": true, "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [974, 1083], "text": ["This determine the depth of the tet layer, relative to the normal directions of the input polygons."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Layer Depth"], "role": "item", "extent": [956, 974], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Sizing"], "extent": [942, 956], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1135, 1267], "text": ["All input primitives are preserved in the output. New tetrahedra are added and may share points with the input primitives."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Preserve Input Geometry"], "role": "item", "extent": [1105, 1135], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Output Geometry"], "extent": [1083, 1105], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1267, 1289], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tetembed", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/tetembed"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1289, 1313], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tetconform", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/tetconform"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1313, 1333], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/remesh", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/remesh"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1333, 1353], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/divide", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/divide"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1353, 1377], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polyreduce", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/polyreduce"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1377, 1406], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [930, 942], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}], "summary": ["Creates a layer of tetrahedra adjacent to a polygon mesh."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "tetrahedralize, solid object, tet mesh, skin, tissue", "since": "16.0", "namespace": null, "internal": "tetlayer", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/tetlayer"}, "title": ["Tet Layer"]}